{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SnappThemingColorDeclarations","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" = ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SnappThemingDeclarations","preciseIdentifier":"s:12SnappTheming0aB12DeclarationsV","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/snapptheming.SnappTheming\/documentation\/SnappTheming\/SnappThemingDeclarations"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"SnappThemingColorRepresentation","preciseIdentifier":"s:12SnappTheming0aB19ColorRepresentationO","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/snapptheming.SnappTheming\/documentation\/SnappTheming\/SnappThemingColorRepresentation"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SnappThemingColorConfiguration","preciseIdentifier":"s:12SnappTheming0aB18ColorConfigurationV","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/snapptheming.SnappTheming\/documentation\/SnappTheming\/SnappThemingColorConfiguration"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Colors can be declared as child properties of the root-level ","type":"text"},{"code":"colors","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property, as follows:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","    \"colors\": {","        \"appPrimary\": \"#FF0000\"","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The framework supports HEX-ecoded RGB, RGBA and ARGB notations. All of the following are valid entries:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["{","    \"colors\": {","        \"appPrimary\": \"#FF0000\",","        \"appSecondary\": \"#FF00000A\",","        \"appTertiary\": \"#0AFF0000\",","        \"appQuaternary\": \"#0F0\"","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Certain themes may require support for the system dark mode. In such cases, you can utilize the following annotation (again, HEX, RGBA, and ARGB colors are all supported here):"}]},{"code":["{","    \"colors\": {","        \"appPrimary\": {","            \"light\": \"#FF0000\", ","            \"dark\": \"#CC0000\"","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"json","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The mixing of color declaration styles is also supported. The following is a valid construct:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","    \"colors\": {","        \"appPrimary\": {","            \"light\": \"#FF0000\", ","            \"dark\": \"#CC0000\"","        },","        \"appSecondary\": \"#FF00000A\",","    }","}"]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the example above the "},{"code":"appSecondary","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" color will be initialized with a value of ","type":"text"},{"code":"#FF00000A","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which will be used in both the system light and dark modes","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Providing-hints-on-the-color-format-to-the-parser","text":"Providing hints on the color format to the parser"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In general, decoding colors correctly should be automatic. The parser can handle various HEX-driven color declarations. Both "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#FFF"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#FFFFFF"},{"type":"text","text":" annotations will be recognized and supported by default. The parser also defaults to recognizing RGBA color annotations (e.g., "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#FFFFFF0A"},{"type":"text","text":"). If you need to support ARGB, please provide the correct value to the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/snapptheming.SnappTheming\/documentation\/SnappTheming\/SnappThemingParserConfiguration\/colorFormat","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" property of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/snapptheming.SnappTheming\/documentation\/SnappTheming\/SnappThemingParserConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (see "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/snapptheming.SnappTheming\/documentation\/SnappTheming\/SnappThemingColorFormat","isActive":true},{"text":" for the list of supported values).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/snapptheming.SnappTheming\/documentation\/SnappTheming"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/snapptheming\/snappthemingcolordeclarations"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Responsible for managing and resolving color tokens, including static colors and dynamic system colors, with support for light\/dark mode.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Type Alias","role":"symbol","title":"SnappThemingColorDeclarations","symbolKind":"typealias","externalID":"s:12SnappTheming0aB17ColorDeclarationsa","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnappThemingColorDeclarations"}],"modules":[{"name":"SnappTheming"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SnappThemingColorDeclarations","kind":"identifier"}]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/snapptheming.SnappTheming\/documentation\/SnappTheming\/SnappThemingColorDeclarations","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://snapptheming.SnappTheming/documentation/SnappTheming/SnappThemingColorRepresentation":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A representation of color in the SnappTheming framework."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/snapptheming.SnappTheming\/documentation\/SnappTheming\/SnappThemingColorRepresentation","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SnappThemingColorRepresentation","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitl